Project Context: Trainee Management System
1. Project Vision
The Trainee Management System is designed to provide transparency and structure to the internship/training process. It facilitates daily interaction between Mentors and Trainees through automated task assignments, daily progress reporting, and performance tracking.

2. User Roles & Responsibilities
Role A: Trainee (The Learner)
Task Management: View assigned tasks derived from a specific training curriculum.

Daily Reporting: * Document "What was done," "Planned for tomorrow," and "Issues/Blockers."

Log Man-hours spent on specific tasks.

Progress Tracking: Monitor personal completion rates and view feedback from Mentors.

Q&A: Send direct inquiries to Mentors regarding specific tasks or blockers.

Role B: Mentor (The Supervisor)
Curriculum Management: Create training roadmaps (Curricula) by uploading learning materials (PDFs) and defining task templates.

Review & Governance:

Approve or request revisions for Trainees' daily reports.

Provide feedback and grades based on performance and attitude.

Monitoring (Dashboard): Track the real-time status of all assigned Trainees to identify those who are falling behind or facing critical issues.

Account Management: Manage Trainee profiles and system access.

3. Core Business Workflow
Onboarding: A Mentor creates a Trainee account and assigns a specific Curriculum. The system automatically generates a list of Tasks for that Trainee based on the curriculum templates.

Daily Execution: * The Trainee starts a task and logs progress.

At the end of the day, the Trainee submits a Daily Report.

Status Lifecycle: * A report starts as a DRAFT.

Once the Trainee clicks "Submit," it changes to SUBMITTED.

Submission triggers an automated notification to the Mentor via external Chatops (e.g., Slack/Discord).

Review Loop: * The Mentor reviews the report and marks it as APPROVED (closing the task/day) or REVISION_REQUIRED (sending it back to the Trainee for more detail).

Reporting: * Every weekend, the system automatically aggregates all daily data into a Weekly Performance Summary for the Mentor to review.

4. Key Logic Constraints
Data Integrity: Once a report is APPROVED, it cannot be edited by the Trainee.

Consistency: Daily reports must be linked to active tasks to ensure man-hours are tracked against the correct curriculum items.

Automation: Task generation must be handled by the system immediately upon curriculum assignment to prevent manual entry errors.